messages/DiagramBundle.properties.diagram.graph.characteristics.is.acyclic: A graph is called acyclic if it contains no directed cycle
messages/DiagramBundle.properties.diagram.graph.characteristics.is.biparti: A graph is called bipartite if its nodes can be partitioned into two sets such that each edge connects two nodes of different sets
A graph is called planar if it can be drawn on the plane without edge crossings
A graph is called a forest if its connected components are trees
messages/DiagramBundle.properties.diagram.graph.characteristics.is.tree.co: A graph is called a tree if it is an acylic connected graph
